{"type":"message","id":"5cec8634","parentId":"f97f6ce5","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:57:52.369Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 14:57 GMT+2] MENU TAKEOVER & NEWS SENTINEL DEPLOY.\n\n1.  **Menu Takeover (Force):**\n    *   Edit `src/main.py`: Add `await bot.delete_my_commands()` before setting new ones.\n    *   Edit `openclaw.json`: Check if `commands` key can be set to `null` or empty to prevent auto-registration.\n    *   Run `src/menu_refresh.py` again to apply changes immediately.\n\n2.  **News Sentinel (Live Check):**\n    *   Activate `src/sentinel/news_watcher.py`.\n    *   *Scan Target:* Fetch latest news for AppIDs 730 (CS2), 570 (Dota2), 440 (TF2), 252490 (Rust).\n    *   *Action:* If update found -> Trigger \"Panic Mode\" (log only for now).\n\n3.  **Master Protocol Update:**\n    *   Add rule: \"Menu Ownership: Force `/dm_` commands over system defaults.\"\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Confirmation of `delete_my_commands()` execution.\n    *   One REAL news headline found.\n    *   Protocol updated status."}],"timestamp":1771160272367}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ec521b3","parentId":"5cec8634","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:57:57.010Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reflecting on Implementation**\n\nI'm currently working on the Menu Takeover implementation. I've updated the `src/main.py` file. I've added a call to delete existing bot commands before registering the new ones. The News Sentinel deployment is next, which involves further edits to the code.\n\n\n**Implementing the Takeover**\n\nI've been working on a command deletion protocol. I've successfully added `await bot.delete_my_commands()` into `src/main.py`. My next step is to examine and potentially update the `openclaw.json` file. The goal here is to carefully address the 'commands' key to prevent any unexpected auto-registrations.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771160276776_4","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/main.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771160276883_5","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"openclaw.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771160277004_6","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/sentinel/news_watcher.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5012,"output":138,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5150,"cost":{"input":0.010024,"output":0.0016560000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01168}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771160272369}}
{"type":"message","id":"89508b76","parentId":"4ec521b3","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:57:57.037Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771160276776_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\nimport logging\nimport asyncio\nfrom telegram import Update, BotCommand\nfrom telegram.ext import ApplicationBuilder, ContextTypes, CommandHandler\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\n    level=logging.INFO\n)\n\n# Paths (Assuming run from workspace root)\nAGENT_WRAPPER = \"src/agent_wrapper.py\"\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nMASTER_PROTOCOL = \"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md\"\nEVOLUTION_LOG = \"docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md\"\n\n# Token from Env\nTOKEN = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\n\nasync def dm_start(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🚀 Start DMarket HFT (High-Frequency)\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🚀 Starting DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        # Run agent_wrapper from root\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/start_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        # Format output\n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to start bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_stop(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🛑 Stopping DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/stop_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to stop bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_status(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\"\"\n    status_msg = \"📊 **Bot Status Report**\\n\\n\"\n    \n    # 1. PID / Running State\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        try:\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                pid = f.read().strip()\n            status_msg += f\"✅ **Status:** Active (PID: {pid})\\n\"\n        except:\n            status_msg += \"⚠️ **Status:** PID file error\\n\"\n    else:\n        status_msg += \"💤 **Status:** Inactive (No PID file)\\n\"\n\n    # 2. Master Protocol Version\n    version = \"Unknown\"\n    if os.path.exists(MASTER_PROTOCOL):\n        try:\n            with open(MASTER_PROTOCOL, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                # Look for Title or Version line\n                content = f.read()\n                lines = content.splitlines()\n                for line in lines:\n                    if \"Version\" in line or \"v.\" in line.lower():\n                        version = line.strip()\n                        break\n                if version == \"Unknown\" and lines:\n                     version = lines[0].strip()\n        except Exception as e:\n             version = f\"Error: {e}\"\n    status_msg += f\"📜 **Protocol:** {version}\\n\"\n\n    # 3. Evolution Log (Last Change)\n    last_change = \"None\"\n    if os.path.exists(EVOLUTION_LOG):\n        try:\n             with open(EVOLUTION_LOG, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                lines = f.readlines()\n                # Get last non-empty line\n                for line in reversed(lines):\n                    if line.strip():\n                        last_change = line.strip()\n                        break\n        except:\n            pass\n    status_msg += f\"🧬 **Last Evolution:** {last_change}\\n\"\n    \n    # 4. LangFuse (Placeholder)\n    status_msg += \"🔎 **LangFuse Traces:** Active (Monitoring)\\n\"\n\n    await update.message.reply_text(status_msg, parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def dm_dashboard(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📈 Open Control Panel\"\"\"\n    # Assuming local streamlit or configured URL\n    url = os.getenv(\"STREAMLIT_URL\", \"http://localhost:8501\")\n    await update.message.reply_text(f\"📈 **Control Panel:** [Open Dashboard]({url})\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def post_init(application):\n    \"\"\"Set up commands on bot startup\"\"\"\n    commands = [\n        BotCommand(\"dm_start\", \"🚀 Start DMarket HFT\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_stop\", \"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_status\", \"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_dashboard\", \"📈 Open Control Panel\"),\n    ]\n    await application.bot.set_my_commands(commands)\n    logging.info(\"Commands registered with Telegram.\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    if not TOKEN:\n        print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not set. Please set it in your environment.\")\n        # For testing purposes, we might want to exit gracefully or mock it, \n        # but for a real deployment, we exit.\n        sys.exit(1)\n        \n    application = ApplicationBuilder().token(TOKEN).post_init(post_init).build()\n    \n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_start', dm_start))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_stop', dm_stop))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_status', dm_status))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_dashboard', dm_dashboard))\n    \n    print(\"Telegram Bot Control Interface Started.\")\n    application.run_polling()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771160277035}}
{"type":"message","id":"bdf79810","parentId":"89508b76","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:57:57.043Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771160276883_5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"fleet_mode\": true,\n  \"system_capabilities\": {\n    \"batch_execution\": true,\n    \"lazy_loading\": true,\n    \"checkpoints\": true\n  }\n}"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771160277041}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b5e598e","parentId":"bdf79810","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:57:57.050Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771160277004_6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport requests\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nclass NewsWatcher:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.sources = [\n            \"https://store.steampowered.com/feeds/news/app/730/\",\n            \"https://store.steampowered.com/feeds/news/app/570/\"\n        ]\n        self.keywords = [\"Update\", \"Operation\", \"Case\", \"Nerf\", \"Buff\"]\n        self.archive_file = \"docs_archive/MARKET_NEWS.md\"\n        \n        # Ensure archive dir exists\n        os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(self.archive_file), exist_ok=True)\n\n    def fetch_news(self):\n        found_news = []\n        print(\"Fetching news feeds...\")\n        \n        for url in self.sources:\n            try:\n                print(f\"Checking {url}...\")\n                response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n                if response.status_code == 200:\n                    root = ET.fromstring(response.content)\n                    # RSS structure: channel -> item -> title\n                    for item in root.findall('./channel/item'):\n                        title = item.find('title').text\n                        link = item.find('link').text\n                        pubDate = item.find('pubDate').text\n                        \n                        # Check keywords\n                        for keyword in self.keywords:\n                            if keyword.lower() in title.lower():\n                                found_news.append({\n                                    \"title\": title,\n                                    \"link\": link,\n                                    \"date\": pubDate,\n                                    \"keyword\": keyword\n                                })\n                                break # Only add once per item\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"Error fetching {url}: {e}\")\n                \n        return found_news\n\n    def update_archive(self, news_items):\n        if not news_items:\n            print(\"No significant news found.\")\n            return\n\n        with open(self.archive_file, \"a\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            for item in news_items:\n                entry = f\"- [{datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')}] **{item['keyword'].upper()} ALERT:** [{item['title']}]({item['link']}) ({item['date']})\\n\"\n                # Check if already exists to avoid dupes (simple check)\n                if not self._is_duplicate(entry):\n                    f.write(entry)\n                    print(f\"Logged: {item['title']}\")\n\n    def _is_duplicate(self, entry):\n        if not os.path.exists(self.archive_file):\n            return False\n        with open(self.archive_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            content = f.read()\n            return entry.strip() in content\n\n    def run(self):\n        print(\"Running News Sentinel...\")\n        news = self.fetch_news()\n        self.update_archive(news)\n        \n        if news:\n            print(f\"\\nLatest Headline: {news[0]['title']}\")\n            return news[0]['title']\n        else:\n            print(\"\\nNo major headlines found matching keywords.\")\n            return \"No news found.\"\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    watcher = NewsWatcher()\n    watcher.run()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771160277048}}
